  "id": "algorithm_001",
  "name": "HMA Trend Crossover Strategy",
  "description": "This trading algorithm utilizes the crossover of the 12-period and 36-period Hull Moving Averages (HMA) on 30-minute bars to identify potential long and short positions. A long position is initiated when the 12-period HMA crosses above the 36-period HMA, while a short position is triggered when the 12-period HMA crosses below the 36-period HMA, confirmed by the Directional Movement Index.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Design an intermediate TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Python that trades long or short based on the crossover of the 12-period and 36-period Hull Moving Averages (HMA) on 30-minute bars. Enter a long position when the 12-period HMA crosses above the 36-period HMA, and enter short when the 12-period HMA crosses below the 36-period HMA. Require confirmation from the Directional Movement Index (DMI): only take long trades if the Plus DI is above the Minus DI and ADX is above 20; only take short trades if the Minus DI is above the Plus DI and ADX is above 20. Exit all positions when the cross reverses or if price closes beyond a trailing stop set at 1.8 times the 14-period Average True Range (ATR) from the entry price.",
